('Closing Reception of All Things Considered Exhibition', 'Art and Design', 'Celebrate the end of the year with this brilliant showcase from our rising Visual Arts graduates! This exhibition marks the culmination of their degree, launching their creative journeys. Each student presents a cohesive body of artwork in the Finley Galleries, our final exhibition of the Fall 2025 semester. Join us on Wednesday, April 30 at 6pm to meet the artists at the closing reception. \n Â  \n All Things Considered  features an impressive range of interdisciplinary approaches: mixed-media sculpture, large-scale painting, hand-sewn textiles, ceramics, video projection, photography, and room-sized installations. 45 Visual Arts graduates invite you to explore their creative research and current concerns, on view through these vibrant capstone projects!Â  On view from April 24 till April 30, 2025.Â  \n Exhibiting Artists: Section 1:  Santiago Arcila, Kelly Arita, Sabrina Gatti, Ian Hagen, Jiapsi Juarez-Cipriano, Bryana Martinez, Agnieszka Palka, Krisha Ravishankar, Jin Scheef, Anacia Sessoms, Walaa Shaabneh, Julea Sorrentino, Katie Weuste, Margo Wittlinger, Joseph Visco \n Section 2:  Jivon Batres, Nick Cruz, Genesis Garcia-Morales, Tevin Gomez, Lauryn Jeffrey, Bralen Jones, Aaron Leung, Emily Luh, Lara Maisonneuve, Gabriel Rodriguez, Amaya Tiozon, Sadie Vizcaino, Odessa Whitlock, Brendan Wilsea \n Â  \n Section 3:  Frankie Christie, Paola Cruz, Gina DeMartino, Marlena Holston, Gabriel Marano, Jonathan Muruzumbay, Quara Phillips-Hill, Edward Puello, Meghan Sibert, Brion Spruill, Antonia Sussina, Kimberly Triana Vallejo, Grace Whitteaker, Zoe Yeung, Cedric Yoo, Claudia Zuraw \n Â  \n All Things Considered BA Visual Arts Thesis Exhibition Finley Gallery, Finley Hall Exhibition dates: April 24-30, 2025 Closing Reception: Wednesday April 30, 6-8pm', '2025-04-30 22:00:00', '2025-05-01 00:00:00', 1576, 'Finley Gallery, Finley Hall'),
