('Embed Library Resources in Canvas', 'Sprague Library', 'In this hands-on session, you`ll learn how to quickly and easily embed library resources such as databases, journals, e-books, articles and streaming video into your Canvas course.Â We`ll walk you through permalinking and creating persistent links to prompt your students to log in and access library content hassle-free. We`ll also cover adding a librarian to your course and demonstrate the Library Resources tab in Canvas. \n \n RelatedÂ LibGuide:Â  Canvas and Library Integration by Bill Vincenti \n Register Here:Â https://montclair.libcal.com/event/14544735', '2025-05-05 14:30:00', '2025-05-05 16:30:00', 1651, 'Online'),
('Denim Day 2025: Mind the Gaps, Move Forward', 'University Police Department', 'April is Sexual Assault Awareness Month, and together, we can break the silence.  The Montclair State University Police Department and the Office for Social Justice and Diversity are committed to fostering a campus where survivors feel heard, supported, and empowered.  It starts with believing. It starts with you.  By offering a safe and affirming response to those who disclose gender-based and sexual violence, we can create lasting change. Letâ€™s stand together to end the cycle of silenceâ€”because  every voice matters, and every action counts \n Denim Day is recognized internationally as a day of action and awareness, encouraging people to wear denim to challenge victim-blaming and educate others about sexual violence.  This year, Denim Day falls on Wednesday, April 30, 2025. \n The University Police and  Office for Social Justice and Diversity and the newly formed Office of Advocacy and Community Resilience , in partnership with over 30 campus and local community organizations, invites you to join us  from 9 a.m. to 12 p.m. at the Amphitheater  for a powerful awareness event honoring survivors and increasing awareness of available resources. \n Despite the  gaps  that still exist in the criminal justice system, in resources, and in prevention education,  we will move forward together  as a community. As part of this commitment, we will walk  one mile around campus in solidarity with survivors.', '2025-04-30 13:00:00', '2025-04-30 15:00:00', 1566, 'Meet at the Amphitheater'),
('Rec Nights - Denim Day Decorating', 'Campus Recreation', 'Every year, Denim Day is observed to raise awareness of sexual assault in general among both participants and the general public. Join us as we celebrate Denim Day by decorating everything denim and learning more about its history. Bring your own denim objects to embellish or select from our selection of hats and bags made of denim. \n \n \n How do I sign-up? \n \n Registration is not required \n FREE for students with a valid Montclair State ID \n \n Where and when? \n \n Tuesday, April 29 \n 7pm-9pm, must be checked in by 8:30pm to participate \n Student Recreation Center Lounge', '2025-04-29 23:00:00', '2025-04-30 01:00:00', 1562, 'Student Recreation Center 11C2A - Lobby Lounge'),
