('Spoken Word Night', 'Montclair State University Galleries', 'Meet the artist Layo Bright and come together to share your stories through spoken word, written reflection, and simply listening. This is a space to express yourself freely, connect with others, and celebrate our experiences in the context of the University Galleries` current exhibition  Invasive   Blooms . Writing materials & supplies will be provided. \n About the Exhibition on view Through sculpture, artist Layo Bright delves into themes of time, feminism, migration, and the African diaspora. Her practice employs blown, fused, and cast glass processes, along with mixed media, such as textiles, wood, and ceramics, to engage ideas about individual and community identity. \n This exhibition features recent and new works, including the debut of an hourglass sculpture that marks the passage of time and Bloom portraits created in collaboration with the Montclair State University community. These portraits incorporate casts of faces of students, faculty, and staff, accompanied by their migration stories and reflections on identity, traditions, beliefs, and empowerment.  Learn more', '2025-04-29 22:30:00', '2025-04-30 00:30:00', 1561, 'Kasser Theater Lobby'),
